This paper deals with a generative model for human planning under the Bayesian Inverse Reinforcement Learning (BIRL) framework, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as Bayesian inference and hierarchical reinforcement learning, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the prediction of human behavior in a game, which falls under the sub-field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of scaling up the framework, which is related to the sub-field of control systems (cs.SY).
